divs: Sighting Detailswhile observing various objects both in groups of up to three and singly, various objects flash, blink, emit light patterns of various complexities and respond directly when illuminated by a hand laser, by flashing in sequences and as patterned surfaces on the craft themselves. at one point a very large silver lighted object came in from the west towards mt. rainier. when the object was directly overhead and into the 1 0'clock position it suddenly just became two separate objects about the same size but not quite. each object flashed brilliantly, faded, flashed very bright and then the objects traveled in different directions. one going north east, the other south west like a huge Y where they forked in the sky so to speak. it was a wonderful display.
Object Flight Path: Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering,Other
Summary: while observing multiple objects fly over singly and as groups west of mt rainier with flashes, blinks & "textured" lights a large object split into two object with different directions
